The paper discusses a hybrid architecture that combines IP and ICN, which is primarily related to networking (cs.NI). The paper also discusses the benefits of ICN in terms of performance and resilience, which could fall under the categories of architecture (cs.AR), cryptography and security (cs.CR), distributed, parallel, and cluster computing (cs.DC), and information theory (cs.IT).
